author: stefan2
msg: (Basically) eliminate the remaining CPU processing overhead of FSFS
format 7 over format 6 in non-block-read mode.
We simply don't prefetch index data in non-block-read mode anymore.
Since we will only ever read index data when we had to open the file
anyway to read some of its content, reading non-cached index parts
is relatively cheap (seek and read operations only).
